                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I have finally figured it out.  I know, I'm a little slow, but it is coming up on Fall break and my mind is elsewhere.  Sorry if this has already be mentioned, but I didn't really see it when I searched.
<br />

<br />
We were supposed to get Advanced Dire Charm.  When Dire Charm first came out, it was a little extra nearly risk-free DPS.  The mobs were in the normal experience zones, but were lower level mobs.
<br />

<br />
In PoP, pre-gimped mobs were put in some zones (PoI, PoS, PoT, CoD, HoH, Tactics, PoE, PoA, and maybe some others I've missed).  They are really a little better than a lvl 46 mob should be, but gimped compared to the normal mobs in the zone.
<br />

<br />
So, with OoW, they decided to make normal mobs DC-able, but severly gimp them when they are charmed.  Again, a little extra relatively risk-free DPS.  Quite a reasonable solution for ADC, but with somewhat more risk than current DC (heavy hitting former ADC pet now run amok in the raid if the enchanter dies).
<br />

<br />
Now, charm had to be reigned in some, but SOE couldn't figure out how to do it.  Finally, they look at the ADC solution, kill ADC, and make charm really ADC -- with heavy risk.  The ADC solution was balanced for ADC, but severely flawed for normal charm.
<br />

<br />
So, give us ADC and kill the charm line.  At the very least, it would be honest.  Or, give us ADC and talk with us to get a decent solution for normal charm.
<br />

<br />
Or, just talk with us.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37024" target="_blank" class="postlink">Serius</a>
<br />
''Dead enchanters take no faction hits''
<br />
Member, Code of Silence
<br />
Luclin Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
