                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My point of this whole thread is that what we have been given as "Charm" by SOE is really Dire Charm -- with a whole lotta risk.  SOE should admit it and make it dire charm.  Then either eliminate the entire charm line or work out a way for it to be fun for us, but not too fun.
<br />

<br />
In a couple of broken zones, charm is very much overpowering.  But only successful if you design the group around charm.  I've heard from druids who were completely happy as they could now get in a group and contribute.  And paladins can find a group, not as weak tank, but as charm support.  Of course, if druids and paladins are happy, then someone else has to be unhappy.  Apparently, it was the magicians.
<br />

<br />
If all of EQ were this way, it would be a bad thing.  Unfortunately, everyone who wants to progress in GoD has to go through this zone.  If the mountain trials had been in some backwater zone that groups (the "right kind") would sometimes go for experience, then we would never have heard about it.
<br />

<br />
Now, that is what is really at stake here.  Has EQ become so homogenized that every encounter in every zone has to have the same group makeup?  Possibly so.  And, enchanters may now be looking from the outside.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37024" target="_blank" class="postlink">Serius</a>
<br />
''Dead enchanters take no faction hits''
<br />
