                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Enchanters have always been a situational DPS class. Its not right to say any class in EQ is "not a dps" class since they all do damage in some form.
<br />

<br />
Enchanters get their dps from charm pets, which are nothing at all like summoned pets. How they are gotten and how they are kept, the risk and reward are all entirely different. The ONLY thing they have in common is the word "pet"; and from that linguistic limitation mages demand permanent and massive nerfs without removing the risks as well. All based on some completely arbitrary word "pet".
<br />

<br />
I like the idea of the ADC charm because it would be a reasonable fix to the issues as they sit now. There are many limitations to using Dire Charms:
<br />

<br />
* Long time between recasts
<br />
* Pets break on dispells
<br />
* Pets break on invises
<br />
* Pets don't poof like mage pets when they break, they attack the charmer and the group.
<br />
* Charmers death releases the pet onto the remaining group.
<br />
* A broken charm pet is very upset with the charmer. 
<br />
* Moving about in a zone using invis isnt an option, since that breaks the charm. So, you have to fight your way everywhere.
<br />
* If you need to zone for some reason, your can't use DC again until it pops. This is an issue for people who leave a zone often to help friends or buff guildmates. Having yoru DC pet up means a large restriction on you since leaving the zone has consequences to your gameplay. This is extactly the opposite of a mage where the summoned pet follows them anywhere, even while invisible.
<br />

<br />
The number of restrictions on charming and Dire charms more than makes up for the dps advantage - in fact it is the reason the dps should be higher than summoned pets.
<br />

<br />
I play both a mage and an enchanter (well, I have 2 mages and one enchanter).
<br />

<br />
ADC is a viable alternative to all these charm restrictions put in recently.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
