                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hey now, a personal attack every once and a while is nice, but when someone like Zarath actually tries to have a logical discussion about something, it's not nice to call them a troll, ignore them, etc. Other classes are perfectly welcome to talk to us about our class's woes--a better educated norrathian is a better norrathian.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Zarath wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I write my responses without actually reading the thread! It is the only explenation!</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You are, among other things, a summoned pet class. Summoned pets have been a part of your class since the beginning of the game.
<br />

<br />
I am, among other things, a charmed pet class. Charmed pets have been a part of my class since the beginning of the game.
<br />

<br />
Summoned pets are safe, reliable, and cheap, but not as strong. Charmed pets are extremely, unsafe, unreliable, and prohibitively expensive, but much stronger. 
<br />

<br />
Only now change that "much stronger" to "a little less than twice as strong on offense but has lots of hit points", and you'll have the current situtation.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Zarath wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Zarath is a concerned Magician who is wondering why Enchanters think they should have the highest DPS, or even approaching that of an actual DPS class. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
